    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I read the discussion of food magazines you linked to. The comments made me feel rather naive.  I don&#39;t feel that way, but maybe I haven&#39;t been paying close enough attention.  I do miss Gourmet of course. But I also love Saveur (I still remember the photos and descriptions from a Cuba article they did many years ago,) and I do derive inspiration from Bon Appetit. I wrote to BA some months ago telling them I wished they would be more plant-centric, and less-meat-focused, in light of what we know about the environment and the resources that meat necessitates, in additon to the health benefits conferred by consuming a more plant-based diet.  But I do think it&#39;s an appealing and readable magazine, and I find that their recipes in general really work. And as long as that holds true, I don&#39;t care how many chambray shirts they&#39;re wearing.</p>
    </div>

